    <stitle>RECONDITIONING BRAKE DRUMS AND SHOES - REPLACING LINING/BLOCKS - BOLTING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="0">
        <title>BOLTING</title>
        <para>Make sure the bolts are the correct body diameter, length and material or loose lining may result.</para>
        <para>When securing brake lining to shoes, start with the center bolts and work toward the ends (
            <hotlnk document="s04007_12.xml" xrefid="f0400724">Figure 24</hotlnk>). Always use new lock washers. Tighten
            nuts to:
        </para>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <item>
                <para>3/8 inch diameter brass bolts to 18-23 ft. lbs. (24.9-31.6 N&#8226;m).</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>1/4 inch diameter brass bolts to 7-8 ft. lbs. (9.0-11.3 N&#8226;m).</para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
    </svcproc>
